{
  "metadata": {
    "slug": "claude-liam-troubleshooting",
    "title": "Claude, Unstuck",
    "subtitle": "Troubleshooting and Staying Current",
    "channel": "claude-liam",
    "persona": "Kore",
    "folderLabel": "@HumanitariansAI",
    "audience": "Practitioners and makers following the channel's Claude workflows",
    "register": "Teardown",
    "engine": "kokoro",
    "voice": "af_kore",
    "palette": "claude",
    "typography": { "serif": "EB Garamond", "ui": "system sans", "mono": "SF Mono" },
    "model_chip": { "model": "Fable 5", "effort": "High" },
    "source": "books/anthropics/books/claude-cowork-plugins/chapters/ch14-troubleshooting.txt",
    "derived_from": "claude-cowork-plugins.md (Ch.14)",
    "genre": "deep-explainer",
    "one_idea": "When something breaks or doesn't match the screen, don't chase the surface — return to the durable concept (what the plugin is for, what it can and can't do) and check the official docs for the current specifics; the interface dates, the mental model doesn't.",
    "duration_estimate_s": 240,
    "lane_histogram_target": { "VOX": "20-25%", "MANIM": "25-40%", "REMOTION": "30-45%", "CARD": "remainder" }
  },
  "beats": [
    {
      "id": "B00", "act": "COLD OPEN", "lane": "ASK", "scene": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
      "greeting": "Salaam, Kore",
      "props": { "command": "My plugin isn't working — and half the fixes I find online don't match what I'm seeing on my screen. Where do I even start?", "runningText": "thinking…", "output": ["Start from the concept, not the screen —", "then check the official docs for what's current."] },
      "narration_text": "Salaam — this is Kore, in for Humanitarians AI. A plugin misbehaves. A connection fails. Or the guide you're reading doesn't match your screen. The move isn't to chase the surface — it's to return to what the plugin is for, and check the official docs for what's true today.",
      "spark_line": "Concept, then docs."
    },

    { "id": "C01", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "When It Breaks" }, "narration_text": "First, the mindset.", "spark_line": "When It Breaks" },
    {
      "id": "B01", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "illustration/failure-to-abandonment",
      "narration_text": "Things will go wrong. Plugins won't behave as expected, connections drop, results disappoint. The real danger isn't the bug — it's that quiet frustration hardens into abandonment. Diagnosing is how you stay in the game.",
      "show": "A field of small failure marks; one of them hardens and darkens into an X labeled 'abandonment'.",
      "spark_line": "Frustration → abandonment."
    },
    {
      "id": "B02", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/surface_vs_bedrock.mp4",
      "narration_text": "So here's the discipline. The interface is the surface — buttons, menus, wording — and it changes constantly. Underneath sits the durable layer: what the plugin is for, what it can and can't do. You troubleshoot from there.",
      "show": "A shifting surface layer slides and re-labels itself while a solid base line holds perfectly steady beneath it.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "layers", "surface": "interface (changes)", "base": "concept (persists)" },
      "spark_line": "Surface vs. bedrock."
    },

    { "id": "C02", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "The Common Failures" }, "narration_text": "Most breakage takes one of five shapes.", "spark_line": "The Common Failures" },
    {
      "id": "B03", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ChipGrid",
      "narration_text": "Five failures recur. The plugin won't appear. A service won't authenticate. Results come back generic. Everything runs slow. Or a slash-command isn't recognized. Each one has a durable cause — and a durable fix.",
      "show": "Five caution chips resolve onto the stage in turn.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "ChipGrid", "chips": ["Won't appear", "Won't authenticate", "Results generic", "Too slow", "Command not found"] },
      "spark_line": "Five familiar shapes."
    },
    {
      "id": "B04", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "illustration/reopen-reload",
      "narration_text": "Plugin missing after you installed it? Plugins load when Cowork starts — so a mid-session install may not show. Close Cowork completely, reopen it, and it loads. Still nothing? Reinstall it from the plugin's sidebar.",
      "show": "A window closes fully and reopens; on reload, the new plugin tile pops into the active list.",
      "spark_line": "Reopen to reload."
    },
    {
      "id": "B05", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B05.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.45] },
      "narration_text": "A service that won't authenticate almost always means stale credentials — tokens expire, passwords change, access gets revoked. Disconnect the service and reconnect it. And if your company gates third-party access, you may need IT's approval.",
      "show": "A still of an expired key / rejected sign-in; slow push-in.",
      "spark_line": "Credentials go stale.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: an old key or a lock tagged 'expired', documentary duotone. No real logos or product UI."
    },
    {
      "id": "B06", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/threshold_generic_vs_context.mp4",
      "narration_text": "Plugin works, but the results feel generic? That's not a fault — the defaults are deliberately broad. Feed it your context — brand voice, your process, your standards — and the output sharpens past the point where it's actually useful.",
      "show": "A 'specificity' meter sits mid-scale on 'default', then jumps past a threshold to 'your context'.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "threshold", "before": "broad default", "after": "your context" },
      "spark_line": "Broad by default."
    },
    {
      "id": "B07", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/scope_reduces_latency.mp4",
      "narration_text": "Slow operations usually reach outside your machine — a CRM query, a database lookup, web research all cost more than local work. The fix is scope. Ask for one date range, one folder — not everything, everywhere at once.",
      "show": "A huge query set shrinks to a single slice; the latency bar falls right along with it.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "scope", "from": "everything", "to": "one slice", "effect": "latency drops" },
      "spark_line": "Shrink the scope."
    },
    {
      "id": "B08", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "code-block",
      "narration_text": "A slash-command not recognized? Make sure the plugin is installed and enabled — then type a single slash to see every command available right now. If it's still missing, the plugin most likely needs a restart.",
      "show": "Onda code-block: the composer types '/' and a command list resolves; then '/plugins'.",
      "props": { "code": "/\n/plugins" },
      "spark_line": "Type slash, look."
    },

    { "id": "C03", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "The Four Steps" }, "narration_text": "When you're stuck, run the loop.", "spark_line": "The Four Steps" },
    {
      "id": "B09", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "illustration/plugins-panel-toggle",
      "narration_text": "Two quick diagnostics first. Type slash-plugins to see what's installed and active — your first check for anything plugin-related. And if one plugin's misbehaving, disable it, then re-enable it; that reloads its config and clears most transient glitches.",
      "show": "A /plugins panel lists active plugins; one toggles off, then on, and settles.",
      "spark_line": "Check, then toggle."
    },
    {
      "id": "B10", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/four_step_loop.mp4",
      "narration_text": "Then the loop that resolves most problems, in order. One: is the plugin installed and active? Two: are its connections authorized? Three: try a simpler request to isolate the issue. Four: restart Cowork. Most trouble dies inside those four steps.",
      "show": "Four steps light in sequence; a 'resolved' counter climbs toward full as each one clears.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "accumulate", "steps": ["Installed & active", "Connections authorized", "Simpler request", "Restart Cowork"] },
      "spark_line": "Four steps, in order."
    },
    {
      "id": "B11", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B11.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.5] },
      "narration_text": "That third step carries more than its size. Shrink the request until it works — then grow it back. The exact moment it breaks tells you precisely where the problem lives.",
      "show": "A still of one thread lifted clear of a tangled knot — isolation. Slow push toward the freed strand.",
      "spark_line": "Isolate by shrinking.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a single thread pulled clear of a knot, documentary duotone. No product UI."
    },

    { "id": "C04", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "Staying Current" }, "narration_text": "Now the part this whole chapter is really about.", "spark_line": "Staying Current" },
    {
      "id": "B12", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B12.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.5] },
      "narration_text": "Plugins don't sit still. Anthropic improves the official ones; community creators ship their own updates. Each release can add capabilities, fix bugs, or run faster — which means the thing you learned last month may behave differently today.",
      "show": "A still of layered, versioned plates stacking upward — evolution over time. Slow drift up the stack.",
      "spark_line": "Nothing sits still.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: stacked versioned cards or growth rings; no legible version numbers, no product UI."
    },
    {
      "id": "B13", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/interface_dates_concept_holds.mp4",
      "narration_text": "And that's the catch. Cowork handles most updates automatically — so the interface shifts underneath you. Anything written down about the screen starts dating the moment it's written. The concept underneath does not.",
      "show": "A timeline where interface labels churn and re-version tick by tick, while a single concept line runs flat and unbroken beneath them.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "timeline", "churns": "interface labels", "constant": "the concept line" },
      "spark_line": "The screen dates."
    },
    {
      "id": "B14", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "SourceFlow",
      "narration_text": "So verify specifics against sources that stay current. Each plugin's own docs — on its GitHub page and inside Cowork. The plugin directory, where others have already solved your problem. And the official channels — the Anthropic blog and Claude's release notes — for what actually changed.",
      "show": "SourceFlow: three living sources flow in on the left and resolve into 'what's true today' on the right.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "SourceFlow", "sources": ["Plugin docs", "The directory", "Official channels"], "target": "current specifics" },
      "spark_line": "Check the live sources."
    },
    {
      "id": "B15", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B15.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.35], "vox_run": "R1",
        "handoff": { "camera": { "x": 0.5, "y": 0.35, "scale": 1.4 }, "objects": [ { "id": "changelog", "x": 0.5, "y": 0.3, "scale": 1.0, "opacity": 1 } ] } },
      "narration_text": "Make it a habit. Set a monthly reminder to browse the directory and see what's new. And when a plugin you rely on changes, read the changelog — a new feature might be exactly the thing you were missing.",
      "show": "A still of a calendar with a monthly mark, changelog pages fluttering above it. The camera begins a slow descent.",
      "spark_line": "A monthly habit.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a calendar plus loose changelog pages, documentary duotone. Framed to allow a downward move into B15's base. Continuity into B16 (vox_run R1)."
    },
    {
      "id": "B16", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B16.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.7], "vox_run": "R1",
        "handoff": { "camera": { "x": 0.5, "y": 0.7, "scale": 1.7 }, "objects": [ { "id": "foundation", "x": 0.5, "y": 0.72, "scale": 1.0, "opacity": 1 } ] } },
      "narration_text": "Because that's the real skill here. Not memorizing today's menus — but knowing what the plugin is for, and where to check what's current. The interface dates. The mental model doesn't.",
      "show": "The continuous descent lands off the fluttering pages onto a solid foundation block — the durable layer from B02 returns. A terracotta underline draws under 'the mental model'.",
      "spark_line": "The model persists.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: same scene as B15, camera settles on a solid stone foundation beneath the pages. Continuity with B15 (vox_run R1)."
    },

    {
      "id": "V01", "act": "CLOSE", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ClaudeVerdictArtifact",
      "lead_silence_s": 0.5,
      "narration_text": "Let's recap with Claude. When a plugin breaks, don't chase the surface — return to what it's for. Most failures have durable causes: not active, stale credentials, un-customized defaults, external scope, or a needed restart. Four steps clear most of them — active, authorized, simpler, restart. And the interface will keep changing, so verify the specifics in the official docs. The screen dates; the mental model doesn't.",
      "props": { "artifactLines": [ "Don't chase the surface — return to the concept", "Failures usually have durable causes: not active · stale creds · generic defaults · external scope · needs restart", "Four steps: active? authorized? simpler request? restart", "The interface dates — verify specifics in the official docs", "The mental model persists — troubleshoot from there" ] },
      "spark_line": "The verdict."
    },
    {
      "id": "H01", "act": "CLOSE", "lane": "ASK", "scene": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
      "greeting": "Your turn.",
      "props": { "command": "A plugin I installed isn't showing up in Cowork and I'm not sure why. Diagnose it with me: ask whether I restarted Cowork after installing, whether /plugins lists it as active, and whether its connections are authorized. Then give me the four-step check to run in order, and point me to the one official source to check in case something changed.", "runningText": "paste this into Claude…" },
      "narration_text": "Your turn. Paste this into Claude: a plugin I installed isn't showing up, and I'm not sure why — diagnose it with me. Ask whether I restarted after installing, whether slash-plugins lists it as active, and whether its connections are authorized. Then give me the four-step check in order, and point me to the one official source to check in case something changed. It turns this chapter into a troubleshooter that walks your actual problem — run it the next time something breaks.",
      "spark_line": "Run the diagnosis."
    },
    {
      "id": "O01", "act": "CLOSE", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "ClaudeTitleOutro",
      "narration_text": "Claude, Unstuck. Kore, in for Humanitarians AI.",
      "props": { "title": "Claude, Unstuck", "handle": "@HumanitariansAI", "subline": "Troubleshooting and staying current" },
      "spark_line": "Claude, Unstuck"
    }
  ]
}
